ggplot(data = df_name, aes(x = x_var_name, y = y_var_name)) + geom_type() Breaking that down:

First, tell R youre using ggplot() Then, tell it the object name where variables exist (data = df_name) Next, tell it the aesthetics aes() to specify which variables you want to plot Then add a layer for the type of geom (graph type) with geom_*() - for example, geom_point() is a scatterplot, geom_line() is a line graph, geom_col() is a column graph, etc.

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()


## store base as an object
gg_base <- ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors))

gg_base +
  geom_point()

gg_base +
  geom_line()

gg_base +
  geom_col()

gg_base +
  geom_area()

Some common arguments well use first are:

color = or colour =: update point or line colors fill =: update fill color for objects with areas linetype =: update the line type (dashed, long dash, etc.) pch =: update the point style size =: update the element size (e.g.of points or line thickness) alpha =: update element opacity (1 = opaque, 0 = transparent)

gg_base +
  geom_line(
    color = "purple",
    linetype = "dashed"
  )


gg_base + 
  geom_point(color = "purple",
             pch = 17,
             size = 4,
             alpha = 0.5)

gg_base +
  geom_area(aes(fill='orange'))

gg_base + 
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  )

gg_base + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = visitors))

gg_base +
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

gg_base +
  geom_line(linetype = "dotted") +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(
    x = "Year",
    y = "Annual park visitors",
    title = "Channel Islands NP Visitation",
    subtitle = "(1963 - 2016)"
  )

scale format http://www.cookbook-r.com/Graphs/Axes_(ggplot2)/

combine

gg_base +
  geom_line(color = "purple") +
  geom_point(color = "orange",
             aes(size = year),
             alpha = 0.5) +
  theme_minimal()

gg_base +
  geom_col(fill = "orange",
           color = "purple") +
  geom_line(color = "green")

ggplot(data = ca_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()

ggplot(data = ca_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors, group = park_name)) +
  geom_line()

gg_np <- ggplot(data = ca_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors, group = park_name))
gg_np +
  geom_line(show.legend = FALSE) +
  theme_light() + 
  labs(x = "year", y = "annual visitors") +
  facet_wrap(~ park_name)
